      "content": "so you're basically saying the business has to change or fail to accommodate the wage hike? that feels a bit harsh on the entrepreneur. isn't there a massive argument to be made that keeping costs low is what allows these small towns to have any local commerce at all? it feels like you're prioritizing a specific social policy over the actual survival of the local economy.",
